President Trump welcomed the ambassadors and their spouses to the White House, expressing his gratitude for their presence. He praised Ambassador Nikki Haley for her leadership and urged the Security Council to take action against global threats, such as Syria's use of chemical weapons and North Korea's nuclear and ballistic missile programs. Trump emphasized the need for reforms within the United Nations and expressed concern over the disproportionate financial burden placed on the United States. He also expressed his belief in the potential of the United Nations to mediate and solve conflicts. Trump concluded by inviting the ambassadors to take pictures in the Oval Office and have a luncheon to discuss peace and the United Nations.